1.text: Preserve green, healthy leaves throughout the year.

2.text: Prune your strawberry plants after mid- to late February.

3.text: Mow June-bearing strawberries after the last harvest.

4.text: Cut June-bearing matted rows using a rototiller after harvest.

5.text: Remove foliage from crops that bear fruit in the summer.

6.text: Cut old leaves from your plants to get rid of dead weight.

7.text: Remove runners to prevent resources from going to clone plants.

8.text: Remove flower stalks from summer-bearing plants.

9.text: Cut flowers when clusters are small or if you need vegetative growth.

10.text: Remove strawberries to prevent competition between plants.

11.text: Slice off crowns to keep a steady density in highly vegetative plants.
